properties.areaDesc: Central Carbon County; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 7 at 10:45PM MST until February 8 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...SIGNIFICANT TRAVEL IMPACTS WILL PERSIST ALONG AND WEST OF THE
LARAMIE RANGE THROUGH AT LEAST SATURDAY AFTERNOON...

* WHAT...For the Blizzard Warning, blizzard conditions expected.
Total snow accumulations of up to one inch. Dense freezing fog
this evening over the Interstate 80 Summit before strong winds
begin later Saturday morning. Winds gusting as high as 65 mph.
For the Winter Weather Advisory, snow. Additional snow
accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 55
mph.

* WHERE...Central Carbon County east of Rawlins to include the
Interstate 80 Corridor from mile markers 222 to 235.
description here.

* WHEN...For the Blizzard Warning, from 5 AM to 5 PM MST
Saturday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 5 AM MST
Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Strong winds could
cause tree damage.
properties.instruction:
Travel should be restricted to emergencies only. If you must
travel, have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded,
stay with your vehicle.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST SATURDAY... ...BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TO 5 PM MST SATURDAY
